[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " entered the synagogue"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " again, and a man was there who had a withered"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " hand. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They watched"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " closely to see if he would heal him on the Sabbath,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that they could accuse him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So he said to the man who had the withered hand, “Stand up among all these people.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he said to them, “Is it lawful to do good on the Sabbath, or evil, to save a life or destroy it?” But they were silent. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " After looking around"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at them in anger, grieved by the hardness of their hearts,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he said to the man, “Stretch out your hand.” He stretched it out, and his hand was restored."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Pharisees"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went out immediately and began plotting with the Herodians,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as to how they could assassinate"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus went away with his disciples to the sea, and a great multitude from Galilee followed him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And from Judea, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jerusalem,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Idumea, beyond the Jordan River,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and around Tyre"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and Sidon"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a great multitude came to him when they heard about the things he had done. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Because of the crowd, he told his disciples to have a small boat ready for him so the crowd"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " would not press toward him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For he had healed many, so that all who were afflicted with diseases pressed toward him in order to touch him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And whenever the unclean spirits"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " saw him, they fell down before him and cried out, “You are the Son of God.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he sternly ordered them not to make him known."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus went up the mountain"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and called for those he wanted, and they came to him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " appointed twelve (whom he named apostles"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "),"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that they would be with him and he could send them to preach "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and to have authority to cast out demons. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He appointed twelve:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " To Simon"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he gave the name Peter; "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to James and his brother John, the sons of Zebedee,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he gave the name Boanerges (that is, “sons of thunder”); "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and Andrew, Philip, Bartholomew,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Matthew, Thomas,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " James the son of Alphaeus, Thaddaeus,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Simon the Zealot,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and Judas Iscariot,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who betrayed him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went home, and a crowd gathered so that they were not able to eat. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When his family"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " heard this they went out to restrain him, for they said, “He is out of his mind.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The experts in the law"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who came down from Jerusalem"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said, “He is possessed by Beelzebul,”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and, “By the ruler"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of demons he casts out demons.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he called them and spoke to them in parables:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “How can Satan cast out Satan? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " If"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a kingdom is divided against itself, that kingdom will not be able to stand. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " If a house is divided against itself, that house will not be able to stand. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And if Satan rises against himself and is divided, he is not able to stand and his end has come. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But no one is able to enter a strong man’s"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " house and steal his property unless he first ties up the strong man. Then he can thoroughly plunder his house."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I tell you the truth,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " people will be forgiven for all sins, even all the blasphemies they utter."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But whoever blasphemes against the Holy Spirit will never be forgiven, but is guilty of an eternal sin”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (because they said, “He has an unclean spirit”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ")."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " mother and his brothers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came. Standing"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " outside, they sent word to him, to summon him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " A crowd was sitting around him and they said to him, “Look, your mother and your brothers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " are outside looking for you.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He answered them and said, “Who are my mother and my brothers?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And looking at those who were sitting around him in a circle, he said, “Here"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " are my mother and my brothers! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For whoever does the will of God is"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my brother and sister and mother.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]